On pages that contain gadgets with outdated or invalid locations the entire contents of the page fails to load. Only the error message from the gadget is displayed.

For example, an outdated Greenhopper gadget present on a Confluence page will fail to locate the gadget and display only the following error message and none of the other content on the page.

{{Error: RuntimeException occurred while performing an XHTML storage transformation (com.atlassian.confluence.macro.MacroExecutionException: The gadget at https://<host>.atlassian.net/rest/gadgets/1.0/g/com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira:greenhopper-days-remaining-gadget/gadgets/days-remaining.xml was not added to this Confluence instance yet.)}}

The widget should fail gracefully so the rest of the content on the page still loads.

This can be especially painful in instances where the gadget is present on numerous pages and all those pages become broken and must be manually edited one by one to remove the gadget and restore the remaining content.

