As we go through review process, the reviewers may make some changes to pages, but largely they are leaving comments for the author to address.

However, there is no good way now for the author to see a listing of everything that needs to be addressed.  Comments are left on random places in the page, and an author would have to scroll through the entire page to find them.  Emails can be sent, but we receive so many emails about so many things - that just isn't a realistic way to track things.  The author needs to have a way to positively confirm that he/she has addressed all comments.  In my mind, I'm envisioning something similar to Microsoft Word's "Reviewing Pane".

Ideally, there would be some sort of comment listing.  At a minimum, this should be at a page level, but even better would be for a subset of pages or Space level.  I'm thinking subset of pages because we may have several different documents within a space, with different authors responsible for each.  The ability to select one parent item (document) within a space's page tree and see all comments in that area would be extremely useful to ensuring everything gets addressed.

